The Chronicle Mthabisi Tshuma, Showbiz Correspondent AWARD winning actress cum songstress Qeqeshiwe Mntambo will give back to the soothing love she has received from her fans in her arts career through a live recording show set for this month. The show dubbed “Qeqeshiwe Mntambo Unplugged: An Intimate Story”, will be held on May 29 at Ingqungqulu Farm on the outskirts of Bulawayo along Solusi University Road. Qeqe as the actress and singer is fondly known will be supported by acts from Pamela Magariro, Thando Bhala, Thats_X, AshBass, Majoer_Prodi and DJ Skaiva. Commenting on what inspired the fete, Qeqe said: “The show is meant to give back to my fans who’ve supported my musical and acting journey. “The show was inspired by my life in general and things that I’ve managed to overcome as a person and as an artiste. I was supposed to do this show a long time ago and I feel now is the right time to do so. I promise my fans that it’s going to be an exciting and intimate show, so people should be ready for good music from live band performances and lots of fun activities.” -@mthabisi_mthire